**Done.** Here's what was implemented:

**Created `src/components/aiTutor/ProactiveSettings.tsx`**
- Full settings UI for proactive tutor messages, rendered inline within the chat popup
- Enable/disable proactive messages toggle (disables all sub-options when off)
- Browser notifications toggle
- AI-enhanced proactive messages toggle (with privacy notice when enabled)
- Quiet hours (start/end time inputs)
- Reminder time input
- Max messages per day (number input, 1–20 range)
- All 8 message category toggles (`vocabulary-review`, `mistake-review`, `study-plan`, `speaking-practice`, `writing-practice`, `exam-countdown`, `motivation`, `saved-content`) with labels and descriptions
- Local-first privacy notice banner
- Save/Reset buttons with feedback
- Settings persist via `proactiveMessageEngine.updateSettings()` to localStorage
- Closing a category toggle prevents the engine from emitting messages of that type (engine checks `settings.categories[msg.category]` at line 340)

**Modified `src/components/aiTutor/ChatPopup.tsx`**
- Added gear icon button in the header between the online status and the expand button
- Click toggles between chat view and settings panel
- Settings button highlights when active
- `ProactiveSettings` renders in place of the messages/proactive/actions area
- Close button inside settings panel returns to chat view
